The Best Spots in Hoboken + Jersey City for Frozen Drinks 
by  Lara Cohn (https://www.hobokengirl.com/author/laracohn/) 
July 10, 2023   
Lara Cohn (https://www.hobokengirl.com/author/laracohn/) 
July 10, 2023 
0   Facebook (https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.hobokengirl.com/frozen-drinks-alcohol-hoboken-jersey-city-summer/) Twitter (https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Check%20out%20this%20article:%20The%20Best%20Spots%20in%20Hoboken%20%2B%20Jersey%20City%20for%20Frozen%20Drinks%20-%20https://www.hobokengirl.com/frozen-drinks-alcohol-hoboken-jersey-city-summer/) Pinterest Email (mailto:?subject=The%20Best%20Spots%20in%20Hoboken%20+%20Jersey%20City%20for%20Frozen%20Drinks&BODY=https://www.hobokengirl.com/frozen-drinks-alcohol-hoboken-jersey-city-summer/)   
Bars It’s getting hot out quickly. With 90+ degree temp days upon us, the dog days of summer are in full swing. If sipping a frozen drink with a mini umbrella while on a hammock under a shady palm tree is not in the plans for the week/weekend, fret not, as some of Hudson County’s favorite bars and restaurants are serving tons of frosty libations to take you to an island oasis far, far away. We’ve rounded up    places in Hoboken + Jersey City to chill out with a glass of frosé (https://www.hobokengirl.com/hoboken-jersey-city-bars-restaurants-frose/)  or other yummy specialty frozen cocktails all summer long.    Keep reading for a list of the best spots in Hoboken + Jersey City for a frozen drink.      
Disclaimer:  This is a growing list, so please email hello@hobokengirl.com if you know of any that should be included. 
Hoboken 
8th Street Tavern (https://www.instagram.com/8thstreettavern/?fbclid=IwAR2X7Gp8MKiWxJV4ylsvuWXzQrIhlHCGC3agoBDYg-PO6OpmkRbiEy7wYaU)  | 800 Washington Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by 8th Street Tavern Hoboken (@8thstreettavern) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CivMA9iOdqI/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
One of Hoboken’s oldest bars, open since the 1940s, this corner pub has also been known to serve free burgers on Fridays from 4:00PM to 7:00PM during happy hour, and there is also frosé and weekly frozen flavored margaritas, including a mango-flavored one. 
Baja Mexican Cuisine (http://www.bajahoboken.com)  | 104 14th Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Baja Hoboken (@baja.hoboken) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CrmXkEKrtl3/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
This popular taste of the southwest restaurant and bar in uptown Hoboken is the place to go for delicious Mexican grill combos and fun frozen margaritas. The bar boasts an extensive list of fresh fruit flavors from mango and guava to tamarind and passion fruit, with one of the largest collections of 100% Blue Agave Tequilas in the state. 
The Brass Rail (https://www.thebrassrailnj.com)  | 135 Washington Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by The Brass Rail (@thebrassrailnj) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CeYsRUxrFZJ/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
The Brass Rail is a landmark restaurant restored to its original early 1900’s elegance and features frosé specials this summer which can be enjoyed while sitting at its outside sidewalk-side seating or during happy hour with some bar bites. Drinks are $10 each with a choice of guava, mango, passion fruit, raspberry, or strawberry flavors. For a kick to it, add a shot for an additional cost. 
Read More:  3 Summer Drinks We’re Loving in Hoboken: Non-Alcoholic Edition (https://www.hobokengirl.com/summer-drinks-non-alcholic-hoboken-new-jeresey/) 
Charrito’s Taqueria (http://loscharritos.com) | 518 Washington Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Charritos Taqueria Hoboken (@charritostaqueria) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CpBItvRJjc2/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Now rebranded as a taqueria, accompany the spot’s authentic Mexican dishes with a frozen margarita. Charrito’s has a classic margarita but flavor can be added for $1. If going out with friends, Charrito’s has the option of pitchers for $50 of frozen margaritas. 
City Bistro (http://www.citybistrohobokennj.com/)  | 56 14th Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by City Bistro (@citybistrohoboken) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CT-GSmkrD71/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
This American bistro located in Uptown Hoboken is a three-floor restaurant, bar, and lounge. When it’s hot in the city, chill out on the roof with a spiked frozen basil lemonade and friends. Check out the other frozen drinks including a frosé and an aperol spritz, all found at the Rosé Bar on the rooftop. 
East LA (https://www.hobokengirl.com/east-la-hoboken-mexican-restaurant-frozen-margaritas/)  | 508 Washington Street 
An institution in Hoboken since 1983, East LA is known for its dangerously good frozen margaritas from watermelon to raspberry to coconut to cranberry to sangria to pineapple and beyond. Cool off this summer with the special margaritas: a mimosa margarita and rosé margarita. Add some chips and guac your night is set. 
The Madison (https://www.madisonbarandgrill.com)  |1316 Washington Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by The Madison Bar & Grill (@_madisonbarandgrill) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Cs_8TZQRFCA/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
The Madison Bar and Grill is a favorite Hoboken brunch spot but they have a frozen cocktails selection. Choose either their Frose or Gettin’ Figgy With It drinks. 
Mikie Squared Bar + Grill (https://www.mikiesquared.com)  | 616 Washington Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Mikie Squared (@mikiesquared) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CWgNA_zLvS1/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Stop by this casual, patio-fronted Hoboken neighborhood sports bar and grill, in town since 2006, and order a frozen margarita in fab flavors including strawberry — yum. 
Northern Soul Kitchen + Bar (https://www.hobokengirl.com/northern-soul-hoboken-restaurant-drinks/)  | 700 1st Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Northern Soul Kitchen & bar (@northernsoulhoboken) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CtKJJlVRPwB/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Whether attending a live band show, an art show, or even a trivia night, drink the night away with one of Northern Soul’s mango, strawberry, or lime frozen margaritas. 
Orale Mexican Kitchen (https://oralemk.com)  | 1426 Willow Avenue, Hoboken + 341 Grove Street, Jersey City 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Orale Mexican Kitchen (@oralemk) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CtznvTVp1fN/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Both locations offer all-natural, daily flavors of frozen margaritas like blood orange or watermelon. The drinks are awesome to pair with the honey truffle guacamole. 
Pier 13 (https://www.hobokengirl.com/pier-13-opening-2022/)  | 1301 Sinatra Drive 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Pier 13 Hoboken (@pier13hoboken) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Cgwz-9orP12/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
There’s nothing better than enjoying a drink with a view of the Hudson and overlooking the NYC skyline.    Pier 13 (https://www.hobokengirl.com/amanda-bananas-pier-13-food-truck-ice-cream/)  serves up some of the best and most creative frozen drinks in town including the Miami Vice – strawberry mango and raspberry margarita; Margarita  – add raspberry, peach, or mango flavor for $1; Piña Colada; and Strawberry Daiquiri. 
The Stewed Cow (https://www.stewedcow.com)  | 400 Adams Street 
Put on some cowboy boots and enjoy the ride on the bull at this Old Western-style saloon where bourbon makes everything better. The Stewed Cow currently has two frozen cocktails on the specialty cocktail list: The Chameleon, orange vodka, coconut rum, and lime juice; and the Mango Unchained, tequila, mango juice, and chipotle simple syrup. 
Jersey City 
Battello (https://www.hobokengirl.com/battello-frozen-espresso-martini-jersey-city/)  | 502 Washington Boulevard 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Battello Restaurant (@battellojc) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Cd_WI-7LFhx/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Three words: frozen. Espresso. Martini. Enough said. This drink is ideal for a summer day and coffee lovers — and take it from us, it’s an absolute must-try. 
Cellar 335 (https://cellar335.com)  | 335 Newark Avenue 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Cellar 335 Jersey City’s Best Restaurant (@cellar335) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CsY7s-SSwZ2/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
For the dog days of summer, enjoy Cellar 335’s various drink selections. Fighting Five, Tropical Princess, Tiki Derby, are among the drinks to choose from when visiting. 
Harry’s Daughter (https://www.hobokengirl.com/harrys-daughter-jersey-city-bergen-lafayette-restaurant/)  | 339 Communipaw Avenue 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Harry’s Daughter JC (@harrysdaughterjc) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Cklt95muBw-/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
The frozen rum punch is not to be missed at this gem! It’s IG-worthy and delicious. It comes with a slice of pineapple and is styled with a small banana leaf. 
Mathews (https://www.hobokengirl.com/martini-drinks-hoboken-jersey-city/)  | 351 Grove Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Mathews Food and Drink (@mathewsfoodanddrink) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Cr4Nm7VLjVq/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
If there’s one thing Matthew’s knows how to do, it’s cocktails – fun and vibrant ones at that! Opt for the frozen margarita served in a charming vintage-esque glass. 
Smorgasbar | 3 2nd Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by Smorgasbar (@smorgasbar) (https://www.instagram.com/p/ChA8_PsLFt-/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Come cool off at Jersey City’s outdoor waterfront spot with different flavored frozen margaritas. Another selection can be their Frozcal, which is frozen creyente mezcal, passionfruit, and mango. 
See More:  The Best Mimosas in Montclair + Beyond (https://www.themontclairgirl.com/best-mimosas-montclair-nj/) 
Rooftop at Exchange Place (http://rooftopxp.com/)  | 1 Exchange Place 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by RoofTop at Exchange Place (@rooftopatexchangeplace) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CgZ-xoLOkmk/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Enjoy a Frosé – Juliette rosé wine and strawberry beach syrup or a frozen margarita from one of the best views in Jersey City at this multi-level rooftop bar and terrace. 
Rumba Cubana (http://www.rumbacubana.com/jerseycity/)  | 235 Pavonia Avenue 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by RUMBA CUBANA RESTAURANT / NJ (@rumbacubana_official) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CNK5JTUjvAo/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
Take a    trip to Havana (https://www.hobokengirl.com/best-empanada-spots-hoboken-jersey-city/)  without leaving the States. From daiquiris, flavored margaritas, piña coladas topped with a pineapple, and mojitos with fresh cane sugar, Rumba Cubana has it all. If you’re going along the non-alcoholic route, the eatery also offers a non-alcoholic strawberry daiquiri and piña colada. 
White Star Bar (https://www.whitestarbar.com/)  | 179 Warren Street + 230 Brunswick Street 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by White Star Bar (@whitestarbar) (https://www.instagram.com/p/CguQESELNQy/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
White Star is a casual neighborhood American restaurant and craft cocktail bar in Jersey City. White Star Bar has their Frozen Limoncello Spritz at their Warren Street location and Frose at their Hamilton Park location. They both have other drink specials including margaritas and other cocktails. 
Bonus: 
View this post on Instagram 
A post shared by 7-ELEVEn (@7eleven) (https://www.instagram.com/p/Ct95AjOPJUj/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) 
And for those that are looking for a non-alcoholic frozen drink, get to 7-Eleven and be a kid again with that icy refreshment,    the Slurpee (https://www.7-eleven.com/slurpee) which comes in flavors like cherry, Coca-Cola, blue raspberry, piña colada. There are stores located at 422 Washington Street in Hoboken and three locations around Jersey City. 
